
@startuml
class EBike {
  +Frame frame
  +DriveSystem driveSystem
  +Controller controller
}

class Frame {
  -material: String = "steel"
}

class DriveSystem {
  +Motor motor
}

class Motor {
  // No specific attributes or methods mentioned
}

class Battery {
  -storedEnergy: Double (in Wh)
}

class Controller {
  -state: String (On | Off | Charging)
  +controlBattery()
  +commandDriveSystem()
}

class BasicController {
  // Inherits from Controller
}

class AdvancedController {
  -nextInspectionDate: Date
  +estimateNextInspectionDate(): Date
}

// Relationships
EBike "1" --> "1" Frame
EBike "1" --> "1" DriveSystem
EBike "1" --> "1" Controller
DriveSystem "1" --> "1" Motor
EBike "0..1" --> "1" Battery
Controller "1" --> "0..1" Battery
Controller <|-- BasicController
Controller <|-- AdvancedController
@enduml

### Explanation of the Diagram:
- `EBike` contains a single `Frame`, `DriveSystem`, and `Controller`.
- The `Frame` is made of steel.
- The `DriveSystem` has one `Motor`.
- An `EBike` can have **zero or one** `Battery`.
- `Controller` has three possible states (`On`, `Off`, `Charging`) and controls both the battery and the drive system.
- There are two types of controllers: `BasicController` and `AdvancedController`.
- `AdvancedController` has an additional attribute `nextInspectionDate` and a method to estimate it.

